# Node.js 22 Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Use ES modules (`import/export`), not CommonJS (`require`)
- Keep the event loop free — offload CPU-intensive work to worker threads
- Use streams for large data processing (files, HTTP responses)
- Structure: `src/routes/`, `src/services/`, `src/utils/`, `src/config/`

## Async Patterns
- Always use `async/await` over callbacks and `.then()` chains
- Use `Promise.all()` for parallel independent operations
- Use `Promise.allSettled()` when partial failures are acceptable
- Always handle rejected promises — unhandled rejections crash Node 22
- Use `AbortController` for cancellable operations

## Error Handling
- Create custom error classes with status codes and error codes
- Use centralized error handling middleware
- Never expose stack traces in production (`NODE_ENV=production`)
- Log errors with structured logging (pino, winston)
- Use `process.on('uncaughtException')` and `process.on('unhandledRejection')` for graceful shutdown

## Security
- Validate all inputs (use Zod, Joi, or class-validator)
- Sanitize outputs to prevent XSS
- Use helmet.js for HTTP security headers
- Rate limit API endpoints
- Never store secrets in code — use environment variables

## Performance
- Use connection pooling for databases
- Implement caching (Redis) for frequent reads
- Use compression middleware for responses
- Profile with `--inspect` and Chrome DevTools
- Monitor memory leaks with heap snapshots
